    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get the 'both sides' thing but like, if a country's stability totally collapses after you jump in, isn't that pretty much the definition of a failed foreign policy? even if the humanitarian side was okay at first, the end result was a failed state. doesn't that make the whole thing a failure in the long run?",
