      "content": "yeah exactly. so it feels like people who defend it are just focusing on the 'good intentions' part while ignoring the actual wreckage left behind. if we look at it through a realist lens, where national interest and stability are what matter most, wouldn't any intervention that results in a power vacuum and a massive refugee crisis just be objectively classified as a strategic disaster?",
